description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Staffbank for Epsom and St Helier University Hospitals NHS Trust are looking for Bank Pharmacists to join us to cover vacancies and seasonal trends. We are looking for pharmacists who have hospital experience working on wards providing a clinical service. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;All of our wards, except ICU and paediatric areas, have electronic prescribing and medicines administration systems. Training will be provided to enable you to clinically screen, monitor prescriptions, make interventions and order medication electronically.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You must be registered with the General Pharmaceutical Council. Successful applicants will need to complete a full recruitment procedure including Occupational Health, DBS, core skills training and references.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please state on your application the clinical areas you have experience of and consider yourself competent in.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Band 6: PAYE - £24.00 (equivalent to £41,759 if you worked full time for a year, Monday to Friday). Pay rates on Saturdays and Sundays are higher.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 7 available for pharmacists with relevant clinical experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
